thread.title: Brush fire threatened IKEA warehouse, other structures near Spanaway
thread.title_full: Brush fire threatened IKEA warehouse, other structures near Spanaway | The Seattle Times

author: Walker Orenstein
title: Brush fire threatened IKEA warehouse, other structures near Spanaway
text:
A large brush fire threatened an IKEA distribution warehouse and several other structures near Spanaway on Friday afternoon, according to Central Pierce Fire and Rescue.
The fire was under control around 4 p.m, according to a tweet by the department, but at one point it was close enough to the IKEA warehouse that it set off smoke alarms inside, said Assistant Fire Chief Ed Hrivnak.
A diesel tank and chemical storage tanks were close to the fire, which had authorities worried, Hrivnak said. One of several semi-truck trailers outside near the fire was set ablaze.
Hrivnak said the fire, in Frederickson, was called in as a small brush fire, but wind quickly whipped it up to a larger threat. He said battling the fire called for a containment line.
